  <title>Print a definition</title>

  <p>You can print a definition to paper or a file. Before printing, you
  should preview the definition as it would be printed to check that the text
  fits onto the page, especially if you have changed the
  <link xref="print-font">print font</link> size.</p>

  <section id="preview">
    <title>Print preview</title>

    <steps>
      <item>
        <p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">File</gui>
        <gui style="menuitem">Preview</gui></guiseq>.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <p>A print preview window will open which will show you the definition
        exactly as it will be printed.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
	<p>Use the toolbar to browse pages, adjust zoom level and page
	width.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <p>Click the <gui style="button">Print this document</gui> to print
        the definition or close the window to end the preview.</p>
      </item>
    </steps>

    <note>
      <p>The print button in the toolbar may not always work. If it does not
      work for you, close the window and select
      <guiseq><gui style="menu">File</gui>
      <gui style="menuitem">Print</gui></guiseq>.</p>
    </note>

  </section>

  <section id="print">
    <title>Print</title>

    <p>You need to <link href="help:gnome-help/printing">have a printer set
    up</link> to be able to print to paper.</p>

    <steps>
      <item>
        <p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">File</gui>
        <gui style="menuitem">Print</gui>
        <gui style="tab">General</gui></guiseq>.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <p>Select the printer that you want to use from the list of printers
        or select
        <gui href="help:gnome-help/print-to-file">Print to File</gui>.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <p>Chose your <link href="help:gnome-help/printing#paper">printing
        settings</link>.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
        <p>Press <gui style="button">Print</gui> to print the definition.</p>
      </item>
    </steps>

  </section>

